Attribute Importance of each attribute

# Function to calculate the importance of attributes
calculate_importance <- function(model) {
  coefficients <- coef(model)

  screen_size <- coefficients['Screen_85'] - coefficients['Screen_75']
  screen_4K <- coefficients['Resolution_4K'] - 0
  brand <- coefficients['Sony'] - 0
  price <- 0 - coefficients['Price']
  total_range <- sum(c(screen_size, screen_4K, brand, price))

  importance_screen_size <- (screen_size / total_range) * 100
  importance_screen_4K <- (screen_4K / total_range) * 100
  importance_brand <- (brand / total_range) * 100
  importance_price <- (price / total_range) * 100

  Importance_return = list(
    Importance_Screen_Size = importance_screen_size,
    Importance_Screen_4K = importance_screen_4K,
    Importance_Brand = importance_brand,
    Importance_Price = importance_price
  )
}

importance_results <- list()

for (name in names(models)) {
  if (inherits(models[[name]], "lm")) {
    importance_results[[name]] <- calculate_importance(models[[name]])
  } else {
    importance_results[[name]] <- NA
  }
}
importance_df <- do.call(rbind, lapply(importance_results, function(x) do.call(cbind, x)))
rownames(importance_df) <- names(importance_results)

Willingness to pay for each non-price attribute level

# Willingness to pay
# Function to calculate WTP for each attribute
calculate_wtp <- function(model, price_savings) {
  coefficients <- coef(model)
  value_per_util <- price_savings / abs(coefficients['Price'])
  wtp_screen_size <- value_per_util * coefficients['Screen_85']
  wtp_screen_4K <- value_per_util * coefficients['Resolution_4K']
  wtp_brand <- value_per_util * coefficients['Sony']
  return(list(
    WTP_Screen_Size = wtp_screen_size,
    WTP_Screen_4K = wtp_screen_4K,
    WTP_Brand = wtp_brand
  ))
}
price_savings <- 500
wtp_results <- list()
# Loop through each model to calculate WTP
for (name in names(models)) {
  if (inherits(models[[name]], "lm")) {
    wtp_results[[name]] <- calculate_wtp(models[[name]], price_savings)
  } else {
    wtp_results[[name]] <- NA
  }
}
wtp_df <- do.call(rbind, lapply(wtp_results, function(x) do.call(cbind, x)))
rownames(wtp_df) <- names(wtp_results)

#parameter

sony_design = c(1, 1, 0, 1, 1)
sharp_design = c(1, 0, 1, 1, 0)
my_design = c(1,0,1,0,0)
sony_price = 2500
sharp_price = 2000
cost_vector = c(1000,500,1000,250,250)
net_cost = sum(my_design*cost_vector)
market_size = 100

#function for caculate Optimal price,Maximum profit, Market share, plots

library(ggplot2)
calculate_optimal_price_and_profit <- function(my_design, partworths, sony_design, sharp_design, sony_price, sharp_price, cost_vector, market_size) {
  net_cost = sum(my_design * cost_vector)
  price_range = seq(from = 1500, to = 2600, by = 100)
  market_shares = numeric(length(price_range))
  profits = numeric(length(price_range))
  market_share_plot_data = data.frame(Price = price_range, MarketShare = NA)
  profit_plot_data = data.frame(Price = price_range, Profit = NA)
  for (i in seq_along(price_range)) {
    price = price_range[i]
    # Calculate utility
    my_utility = sum(my_design * partworths[1:5]) + partworths[6] * (price - min(price_range)) / (max(price_range) - min(price_range))
    sony_utility = sum(sony_design * partworths[1:5]) + partworths[6] * (sony_price - min(price_range)) / (max(price_range) - min(price_range))
    sharp_utility = sum(sharp_design * partworths[1:5]) + partworths[6] * (sharp_price - min(price_range)) / (max(price_range) - min(price_range))
    # Calculate attractiveness
    my_attractiveness = exp(my_utility)
    sony_attractiveness = exp(sony_utility)
    sharp_attractiveness = exp(sharp_utility)
    total_attractiveness = sum(c(my_attractiveness, sony_attractiveness, sharp_attractiveness))
    # Calculate market share
    my_market_share = my_attractiveness / total_attractiveness
    market_shares[i] = my_market_share
    # Calculate profit
    profit = (price - net_cost) * my_market_share * market_size
    profits[i] = profit
    market_share_plot_data$MarketShare[i] = my_market_share
    profit_plot_data$Profit[i] = profit
  }
  optimal_index = which.max(profits)
  optimal_price = price_range[optimal_index]
  max_profit = profits[optimal_index]
  optimal_market_share = market_shares[optimal_index]
  # Generate plots
  market_share_plot = ggplot(market_share_plot_data, aes(x = Price, y = MarketShare)) +
    geom_line(color = "darkorange") +
    theme_minimal() +
    labs(title = "Market Share vs Price", x = "Price", y = "Market Share")
  
  profit_plot = ggplot(profit_plot_data, aes(x = Price, y = Profit)) +
    geom_line(color = "dodgerblue") +
    theme_minimal() +
    labs(title = "Profit vs Price", x = "Price", y = "Profit")
  return(list(max_profit = max_profit, optimal_price = optimal_price, optimal_market_share = optimal_market_share, market_share_plot = market_share_plot, profit_plot = profit_plot))
}
individuals = names(models)
# Loop through each individual
for (name in individuals) {
  partworths = coef(models[[name]])
  results = calculate_optimal_price_and_profit(my_design, partworths, sony_design, sharp_design, sony_price, sharp_price, cost_vector, market_size)
  max_profit = results$max_profit
  optimal_price = results$optimal_price
  market_share_plot = results$market_share_plot
  profit_plot = results$profit_plot

  # Display the results
  cat("\nResults for", name, ":\n")
  cat("Maximum Profit:", max_profit, "\n")
  cat("Optimal Price:", optimal_price, "\n")
  cat("Optimal Market Share:", results$optimal_market_share, "\n")
  # Optionally display the plots
  print(market_share_plot)
  print(profit_plot)
}
